toJava

public SerializedHolder[] toJava(WSDLHolder wsdl,
                                 Options options)
                          throws JavaHolderException,
                                 java.io.IOException,
                                 WSDLException
Takes a WSDLHolder and returns back the Java representation. The Java representation is returned as a SerializedHolder array. Each element of the array is a SerializedHolder that contains the byte[] representing the Java class and the name of the file in the file system to write to.
Specified by:
toJava in interface JavaWriter
Parameters:
wsdl - The wsdl to transform
options - User encapsulated options
Returns:
SerializedHolder[] this array contains all the java code to be written to disk
